<br />
<font class="post">
Actually I felt the same way when I realized it was 3rd person with waypoints and pointandclicking crappy.  But then after playing it in beta I realized that it was a good thing...  The 3rd person camera is moveable and zoomable so if you really want a kind of first person view (more like a close 3rd person) you can have it...  But its not suggestable.  The 3rd person lets you see whats going on around you...  And in a game like Shadowbane that is pretty much a must.  The other nice thing about the way the game engine works is you dont see the unhittable lagstepping casters...  And in fact melee's have a kind of autofollow/attack.  Combat in this game is very much based on what skills you class has and using them right.  If you think your going to survive being a warrior and never use your root/snare break skill (its freaking awsome) your dead.  But at the same time if you dont watch your stamina as a warrior also, your dead (root/snare break costs stamina).  IMHO its a very balanced game and worth a try if you enjoy PvP. 
</font>
